   Housing Programs and Services

   Community Services and Development (CSD), Department of
   Program:
   Energy Assistance Program funded through U.S. Department of Energy
   (DOE).
   Target Population:
   Low-income as defined by Federal Poverty Guidelines.
   Funds:
   $3 million in DOE funds for FY 97/98. Grant funds are available to
   Community Service Development's network of certified state contractors.
   Services:
   DOE provides free installation of energy conservation measures,
   including minor home repair, for low-income households.
   Link:
   http://www.csd.ca.gov/
   Program.html#Weatherization
   Services Contact:
   A county directory of local CSD Community Based Organization service
   providers is available on the CSD web page.
   Local contacts:
   http://www.csd.ca.gov/
   local.html
   Program:
   Low-Income Home Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP): Energy Assistance
   Program funded through Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS).
   Target Population:
   Low-income as defined by Federal Poverty Guidelines.

   Funds:
   Low-Income Home Energy Assistance Program (LIHEAP) Funds. $47 million
   (LIHEAP funds) FY 97/98 Grant funds are available to Community Service
   Development's network of certified state contractors.
   Services:
   LIHEAP provides free installation of energy conservation measures,
   including minor home repair, and financial assistance with energy bills
   for low-income households.

   Link:
   http://www.csd.ca.gov/
   Program.html#Weatherization

   Services Contact:
   A county directory of local CSD Community Based Organization service
   providers is available on the CSD web page.
   Local contacts:
   http://www.csd.ca.gov/
   local.html
   Housing and Community Development, Department of
   Program:
   Community Development Block Grant (CDBG)

   Target Population:
   Recipients of CDBG-grant funded activities must be at 80% or below of
   county median income. Local program eligibility requirements may vary.

   Funds:
   CDBG provides grants of up to $500,000 per year to small cities
   (population under 50,000) and counties (under 200,000).
   Services:
   Housing, child care, job training and development, transportation,
   medical services, and food banks

   Link:
   CDBG Information
   http://housing.hcd.ca.gov/
   ca/cdbg/hcd261.html

   Services Contact:
   To determine whether there is a CDBG-funded facility or service in your
   city or county contact Susan Kessler at (916) 327-3748
   Social Services, Department of
   Program:
   CalWORKs
   Target Population:
   Low income families with deprivation. Services:
   Cash Aid to help pay for housing, food, and other necessary expenses.
   Link:
   CalWORKS program information
   http://www.dss.cahwnet.gov/
   getser/afdc.html
   Services Contact:
   These funds are allocated directly to County Welfare Departments (CWDs)
   for distribution to eligible families or individuals. Local CWDs list
   http://www.dss.cahwnet.gov/
   wtw/counties1.html
